<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_3007"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/3007-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_3007">STUDENT LOANS&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/4403-4049">truebluetexanq</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">7 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Interest rates for student loans should match/be commensurate with interest rates banks receive for loans between banks.  Especially with the current economy and diffculty in students receiving jobs when they finish college, this would provide more success in the repayment of loans.  If banks are able to have such low interest rates, why not allow students to receive loans via the same "game and playing field".</div>
